Definition: an autosomal recessive form of muscular dystrophy that appears anywhere from late childhood to middle age
Example: characterized by progressive muscular weakness beginning either in the shoulder or pelvic girdle; usually progresses slowly with cardiopulmonary complications in the later stages
Synonyms: muscular_dystrophy, autosomal_recessive_disease, an, autosomal, recessive, form, of, muscular, dystrophy, that, appears, anywhere, from, late, childhood, to, middle, age, characterized, by, progressive, weakness, beginning, either, in, the, shoulder, or, pelvic, girdle, usually, progresses, slowly, with, cardiopulmonary, complications, later, stages
Category: noun.state
